<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="564" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d564">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 033.1100K77/79.]</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Dominican Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Assistant Secretary of
                            State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the Dominican Republic</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-04">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 4, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I take very great pleasure in
                            transmitting to you the cablegram that I received yesterday from the
                            Dominican Government, relative to the journey of his excellency Mr.
                            Knox; it expressly confirms my anticipations, which I have already had
                            the honor to express to you. It reads as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Communicate to the Department of State that the Dominican
                                    Government will receive with the greatest pleasure the visit of
                                    the illustrious Secretary, Mr. Knox. Machado, Secretary.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Fran’co J. Peynado.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>